On 3/11/03 6:28 PM, "bustedbus" <joe(-at-)bustedbus.com> wrote:

> We arein the process of doing a late model canvas in the shop and the old
> stapler isn't cutting it. What kind of stapler is best suited for this
> task(read as is there a stapler that will kill me if I use it wrong?)
> Thanks
> Charles Gould

Charles,

I have used an air stapler with good results. The best thing is that by
regulating the amount of air pressure you control the depth of the staples
in the work. Too much pressure and they will go clear through the plastic
strip.

Scott Lyons
